msgstr ""

#. long description of BeeQueenCage in markdown
#: boxes/generators/beequeencage.py
msgid ""
"Cage box to house a bee queen.\n"
"The default opening on top is suitable for a Nicot queen-rearing cell cup"
" block (CNE2) or a cork plug.\n"
"This makes the cage suitable as a hatching cage.\n"
"\n"
"Holes can be configured per side. The default value of 3.0mm is suitable "
"as air holes, but this can be changed to\n"
"produce queen excluders (4.2mm) or drone excluders (5.2mm). Some space "
"should be left closed to provide cover for\n"
"the young queen against aggressive worker bees.\n"
"\n"
"If required a plug can be added to close the top opening.\n"
"By default it contains a inner cutout to fit a Nicot cell cup (CNE3) "
"making it a wooden alternative to the\n"
"plastic Nicot cell cup block (CNE2).\n"
msgstr ""

